Buckland: Briet: Bibliography. March 26, 2005. Revised Dec 31, 2017.

1

SUZANNE BRIET 1894-1989: CHECKLIST OF WRITINGS compiled by Michael Buckland

Full name: Renée Marie Mélanie Suzanne Briet. Suzanne Briet also wrote as Suzanne Dupuy, Suzanne Dupuy-Briet, and Suzanne Briet-Cartulat.

Caution: This list is not complete. Some of the entries are incomplete. Some of the items have not been verified by physical inspection of the item cited.
Suzanne Briet also wrote as Suzanne Dupuy, Suzanne Dupuy-Briet, and Suzanne Briet-Cartulat.

Bibliographical background Revue des bibliothèques became Archives et bibliothèques until1939, then ABCD: Archives,
Bibliothéques, Collections, Documentation. I.I.D. Communicationes became F.I.D. Communicationes and then, effective vol. 14 (1947): Revue de la
Documentation = Review of Documentation.

Sources: Some sources are indicated in [square brackets] for some of the unverified entries: BN: Online catalog of the Bibliothèque nationale de France. LL: Library Literature. Maack: Maack, Mary Niles. The Lady and the Antelope: Suzanne Briet's Contribution to the French
Documentation Movement. Library Trends 52, No 4 (Spring 2004):719-747. Petitfils: Pierre Petitfils. Notre Présidente d’Honneur. Rimbaud vivant. Bulletin des Amis de Rimbaud 26
(1987): 6-12. A bio-bibliography.

